  "text": "ATM is involved in the initiation of all cell cycle checkpoints following XRT-induced damage. ATR, another PIKK family member, can also phosphorylate most of the substrates, but is especially active after UV-or a high level of XRT-induced DNA damage [CITATION_1] . Corresponding to the different checkpoints, ATM targets different substrates and thus can affect different pathways.",
